        <a href="/media-outlet/rattle" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Rattle</a>
        
    
    


            </div>
            
            
                
                    Elizabeth Johnston AmbroseAFTER MY TEENAGER TRIES TO KILL HERSELF, I DREAM EVERYONE IS TURNING INTO ZOMBIES BUT ALL I CARE ABOUT IS FINDING WARM TORTILLASA ridiculous dream, really. In the mall, hysteric masses rushing the exit and there I am,stepping over half-eaten bodies, jumping Taco Bell’s counter,&nbsp;rummaging for chips and salsa. When I wake, I try to untangle the meaning. Zombies = mindless hunger? Or, appetite for the mundane?
                
                
            
        </div>
    
    
