                    Brent GoodmanMAPSThe other night I spaced a stop signand ran it 60mph and diedbut didn’t. What algebra is this? The night a dusty chalkboardstreaked with moonlight, my life hwy K,hwy 51 N intersecting K in a near perfect Tlike a cardiac monitor flatline, the afterlifethis narrowing gravel road beyond pavementdisappearing into endless juniper and birch. It was very dark and the signs obscured. By heavens no screaming headlightsT-boned me into oblivion.
                
                
            
