                    Maryfrances WagnerBRANDON LANGFORD TALKS THROUGH DETENTIONI’m here because I don’t want a suspension,&nbsp;but I hope you know you caused me to miss my bus. &nbsp;I don’t even understand why I have detention. You tell us to say what we think. I spoke&nbsp;my thoughts, and that’s my right. My daddoes it all the time, freedom of speech,and we cheer. Well, we did. He’s a combat vet,&nbsp;but now he’s in prison for child porn&nbsp;and hitting my mom. She’s glad he’s gone. Do I have to stay here the whole time?
                
                
            
